title: WATCHMEN Episode 5 Breakdown! New Theories and Easter Eggs!
author: Think Story
comment: Dude, “Friend of Nemo” is clearly a reference to Captain Nemo, who fought a giant squid in ‘20,000 Leagues Under the Sea.’ It makes far more sense than Latin for “nobody,” as this group is about people fighting their fear of a giant squid. IMO, of course.
Wade is an interesting character. Hope he doesn’t die.
Arguably the best Watchmen episode so far can't wait for what next.

I figured Veidt would use those corpses to get home. His story parallels the Black Freighter story in the comics where the protagonist escapes a desert island by fashioning a raft from the corpses of his dead shipmates.
I don't think he did it to betray Angela, but more to save her and her family.
